        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 11 at 12:55PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 1254 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from Idaho City to near Blacks
Creek Reservoir. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Idaho City, Lucky Peak Dam, Arrowrock Dam, and Lucky Peak Spring
Shores Marina around 100 PM MDT.
Thorn Creek Summit and Mores Creek Summit around 110 PM MDT.
Twin Springs around 120 PM MDT.
Barber Flat Guard Station around 130 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
